23/01/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- International community High Representative Paddy Ashdown will be touring BiH this week, paying a farewell visit. His mandate expires next week. Ashdown plans to visit Trebinje and Mostar on Monday (23 January), Gorni Vakuf and Banja Luka on Tuesday and Srebrenica on Wednesday. He will be meeting with local officials, members of the business community and average citizens to discuss the changes that have occurred over the past three years and a half. On 1 February, German diplomat Christian Schwarz-Schilling assumes the post. (RTRS, Fena - 22/01/06)
